Nha Toi” is a Vietnamese name that translates to “my home” in English, the name itself conveys a sense of warmth, personal connection, and the delightful feeling of being welcomed into someone’s cozy home. Imagine walking into a place where you feel like you’re stepping into a dear friend’s home. That’s the atmosphere we aim to create at “Nha Toi.”

At Nha Toi, we want every visitor to feel like an extended member of our family. Just like when you’re invited into a friend’s home, you can expect not only the most delicious Vietnamese cuisine but also the comfort and love that goes into every dish. It’s an invitation to explore the flavours of Vietnam while being surrounded by the same comfort and familiarity you’d find at a close friend’s house.

We’re excited to share our love for Vietnamese cuisine with you and to create personal, heartwarming memories together. Welcome to “Nha Toi,” our home, your home.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: Experience Vietnamese excellence at Nha Toi Restaurant paired with the delightful and refreshing Truedan Bubble Tea. Indulge in Southern Vietnamese cuisine and refreshing beverages for an unforgettable dining experience. Visit us today!

attributes.about_this_biz_history: In 1958, two brothers borrowed $600 from their mom to open a pizza place in Wichita, Kansas. They named it Pizza Hut because their sign only had room for eight letters. How profound! Soon, the restaurant grew. Why? The pizza was awesome. The service felt like home. And the customers were treated like family. And we've been delivering that same food and service ever since. For the Love of Pizza Since 1958. From day one, the Carney brothers could look their customers in the eye and promise them the finest pizza in town -- because they knew the farmers who grew the ingredients, and they knew those farmers cared about quality. Since then, our farmers have grown right alongside us, and the ingredients we use are still our highest priority. No one loves pizza more than Pizza Hut. That's why pizza is in our name -- and always will be.
